Altus Group is currently looking for a new Real Estate Valuation Analyst. This position is dedicated to client services and is located in the Dallas offices of Invesco Real Estate. In this position, you will be responsible for all financial analysis for every property within the client portfolios assigned to the analyst. Specific analyses include valuation, asset management, disposition, lease and historical performance analysis. Other responsibilities include the assisting asset management and portfolio management with the external appraisal process and ad hoc analysis. Group Description: The Valuations Group performs all financial analysis for Invesco Real Estate’s US direct real estate portfolio, valued at over $31 billion. The group performs the processes for establishing fair market values for the underlying assets through third party appraisals and internal valuations. These valuations are required for financial reporting, client reporting, and performance benchmarking. The primary property types include office, retail, industrial, and multi-family. The independent group is tasked with the execution of a process designed to value assets with as much objectivity as possible. An important part of the function is to balance the competing perspectives of investment professionals involved in the internal processes to ensure that supportable data is the primary consideration in deriving unbiased valuations. This work is necessary for all of the Advisor’s product lines including open end funds, closed end value add funds, closed end strategic opportunistic funds, an open-end debt fund, and separate account clients. Understanding the structure and investment premises of these funds and their underlying assets will be critical to providing quality work. Key Responsibilities: Perform financial modeling such as discounted cash flow for unleveraged structures. Coordinate with all levels of management to gather and analyze data, summarize findings, and prepare recommendations regarding conclusions. Facilitate the third-party appraisal process as directed by client requirements, including reviewing and auditing the appraisals and writing review comments with market support for findings. Present valuation analyses and assumptions to senior members of asset management and portfolio management. Other duties as assigned. Position Requirements: BA or BS required in Finance, Real Estate, Accounting or Economics, or an area with real estate related coursework Minimum of 1-2 years of experience in the financial analysis of commercial real estate investments and/or appraisal services Intermediate Argus and Excel skills preferred Self-motivated, team oriented and strong time management skills to prioritize deadlines Excellent organizational, interpersonal, oral and written communication skills is essential Must have general grasp of understanding the inputs and outputs of a property-level cash flow Come realize your potential at Altus Group!
